### English Biography
**Yongxin PAN** is a research professor at the Institute of Geology and Geophysics, Chinese Academy of Sciences (CAS), and an academician of the CAS. 
His research interests include **biogeomagnetism**, **Earth’s and planetary magnetic fields**, and habitability. He serves as the project scientist for China’s first Mars Exploration Mission (Tianwen-1) and the co-project scientist for the Macao Science 1 (MSS-1) magnetic satellite mission. He is the editor-in-chief of the *Chinese Journal of Geophysics* and *Earth and Planetary Physics*. 
He is a recipient of the Outstanding Science and Technology Achievement Prize of the Chinese Academy of Sciences, National Innovation Forefront Award, and AGU’s Edward Bullard Lecture Award, among many others.
